## CSS/TailwindCSS Style

### Class Order

```html
<!-- Good: Organized class order -->
<div class="flex items-center justify-between w-full max-w-4xl mx-auto p-6 bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg shadow-md hover:shadow-lg transition-shadow md:flex-col sm:p-4">
  <!-- 1. Layout: flex, items-center, justify-between -->
  <!-- 2. Sizing: w-full, max-w-4xl -->
  <!-- 3. Spacing: mx-auto, p-6 -->
  <!-- 4. Visual: bg-white, border, rounded-lg, shadow-md -->
  <!-- 5. Interactive: hover:shadow-lg, transition-shadow -->
  <!-- 6. Responsive: md:flex-col, sm:p-4 -->
</div>
```

### Custom CSS

```css
/* Good: Use @layer and @apply */
@layer components {
  .btn-primary {
    @apply bg-blue-600 text-white font-semibold py-2 px-4 rounded-lg;
    @apply hover:bg-blue-700 focus:ring-2 focus:ring-blue-500;
    @apply transition-colors;
  }
}

/* Bad: Don't use arbitrary custom CSS */
.btn-primary {
  background-color: #2563eb;
  color: white;
  /* Use Tailwind utilities instead */
}
```

